table abc_extra66.ABC_dict:
  description: "abc ABC.__dict__.__class__.__name__ and ABC.__dict__.__contains__('__abstractmethods__') checks in abccode66 namespace — wave 237 theme: ABC hierarchy deep dive; ABC.__dict__.__class__.__name__=='mappingproxy' (Python class __dict__ is always a mappingproxy); ABC.__dict__.__contains__('__abstractmethods__')==True (ABC sets __abstractmethods__=frozenset() as a class attribute); NEW in extra66: first __dict__.__class__.__name__ and __dict__.__contains__ checks for ABC in the abccode66 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: dict
  id_prefix: abccode66b

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [abc_dict_cls,          ABC.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,     ["mappingproxy"],     true, "ABC.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Python class __dict__ is always a mappingproxy; ABC.__dict__.__class__.__name__ is 'mappingproxy'; NEW in extra66: first __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') check for ABC in the abccode66 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [abc_dict_abstractmethods, ABC.__dict__.__contains__, ["__abstractmethods__"], true, "ABC.__dict__.__contains__('__abstractmethods__') == True — ABC sets __abstractmethods__ = frozenset() as a class attribute to mark itself as concrete; '__abstractmethods__' is in ABC.__dict__; NEW in extra66: first __dict__.__contains__('__abstractmethods__') check for ABC in the abccode66 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]

